# Avoid eager allocations for deferred-use data

Don't collect or clone data that is only needed on a cold path (e.g. error/panic messages). Defer the work to the point of use.

```rust
// ❌ BAD: clones names eagerly even though they're only used in a panic
let names: Vec<String> = items.iter().map(|i| i.name.clone()).collect();
do_work(&items);
result.unwrap_or_else(|| panic!("failed for {}", names.join(", ")));

// ✅ GOOD: build the list only when the panic fires, borrow instead of clone
do_work(&items);
result.unwrap_or_else(|| {
    let names: Vec<_> = items.iter().map(|i| i.name.as_str()).collect();
    panic!("failed for {}", names.join(", "));
});
```

Similarly, prefer iterating a borrowed collection directly over collecting into an intermediate `Vec` when a single pass suffices.
